					<item>
				<guid>http://bvs.wikidot.com/forum/t-53127#post-145723</guid>
				<title>Re: Arena weirdness</title>
				<link>http://bvs.wikidot.com/forum/t-53127/arena-weirdness#post-145723</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 15 Apr 2008 16:34:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>BvS-Uzuki</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>78144</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think they take the ratios of your actual stats and then make them a ratio of your arena stats.</p> <p>Ie, if (roughly) 33% of your stats are gen, 33% are nin, and 33% are tai, you get a standard 3/3/3 setup. But if 66% of your stats are nin, 22% are tai, and 11% gen, you'll have a 6/2/1 setup. 44%/44%/22% would result in 4/4/2, etc.</p> <p>I think.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
